      <ResourceHeader>
         <ResourceName>Surface meteorological data at Shigaraki MU Observatory (GIF format)</ResourceName>
         <ReleaseDate>2016-09-22T08:38:00</ReleaseDate>
         <Description>The time-series plot of surface meteorological data taken by the Automatic Weather Station (AWS) at Shigaraki MU Observatory in Shiga Prefecture, Japan (34.86N, 136.11E, 385m MSL), which has been operated on August 8, 1994. This plot includes pressure, temperature, relative humidity, wind velocity, wind direction and rain amount. File names are composed of (year)(month)(day).gif (daily plot), (year)(month).gif (monthly plot) and (year).gif (yearly plot). Local time (UT + 09:00) is used for time data.</Description>
         <Acknowledgement>If you acquire surface meteorological data, we ask that you acknowledge us in your use of the data. This may be done by including text such as surface meteorological data were provided by Research Institute for Sustainable Humanosphere (RISH) of Kyoto University. We would also appreciate receiving a copy of the relevant publications.</Acknowledgement>
